Sixteen students from Busia on Thursday benefited from the Wings to Fly scholarship program funded by the Equity Group Foundation. Half of the beneficiaries were selected by the Busia town branch of the foundation while the others came from Malaba. Busia branch manager Oscar Masinde said only deserving applicants were selected. He said  the recipients will undergo a three-day
induction and training in Nairobi before the official commissioning of the
program on January 4, 2018. Masinde said  successful 
students have been awarded
full secondary school scholarships  following their exemplary  performance in KCPE exam. Busia Deputy
Governor Moses Mulomi thanked the foundation for the scholarship. He urged the students to be good ambassadors of the county. County director of education Gachungi Muriithi told the students to concentrate on their studies.